column168: XPO Logistics terminal XSA experienced a UN1760 Clothesline Fresh BLD 2 release from a 5-gallon poly pail and a Non-Regulated Xcelente release from a 2-liter poly jug. ERTS dispatched contractors to conduct cleanup. Contractors arrived onsite and confirmed all 5-gallons of the UN1760 Clothesline Fresh BLD 2 released as all as all 2-liters of the Xcelente released together. The products impacted a 12’ x 4’ area of the trailer floor and a 12’ x 4’ area of the concrete lot below due to forklift punctures. Absorbents were deployed and worked into the impacted areas. The damaged empty jugs and spend absorbents were then collected into (2) 55-gallon poly drums. The waste was staged onsite for terminal personnel to manage.

column168: XPO Logistics terminal UPH experienced a UN2922 AB-73 release from a 5-gallon poly pail. ERTS dispatched contractors to conduct cleanup operations. Contractors arrived onsite and confirmed approximately 0.5-gallons of material released to a 1’ x 1’ area of the dock floor due to a pinhole puncture. The damaged pail was placed into a 55-gallon poly drum. Spill Fighter was then utilized to neutralize the impacted area. All impacted pads, cardboard, and cleanup debris were containerized into a second 55-gallon poly drum. The waste was staged onsite for terminal personnel to manage.

column42: HYDROCHLORIC ACID
column168: On September 1, 2023, one (1) 5-gallon pail of UN1789 was crushed during transit and released approximately five (5) gallons of product to the trailer interior. R+L Carriers retained Cura Emergency Services, LC who dispatched a crew from Environmental Works, Inc. (EWI) to remediate the impacted site. EWI personnel deployed neutralizing, granular absorbents to the impacted trailer floor and swept them in with hand tools. All freight was wiped down and repalletized for further handling by R+L terminal personnel. All spent absorbents, cleanup debris, and the empty, damaged 5-gallon pail were collected and containerized into three (3) 55-gallon drum that was labeled and staged in the terminal's waste holding room.
column169: NO COMMENTS PROVIDED

column42: ACETONE
column168: On September 1, 2023, one (1) 5-gallon bucket of acetone was damaged during transit and released approximately five (5) gallons of product to the trailer interior and pavement beneath. R+L Carriers retained Cura Emergency Services, LC who dispatched a crew from ES&H to remediate the impacted site.  Crews observed that the released material evaporated prior to their arrival and there was no recoverable material remaining in the trailer. One (1) 5-gallon bucket of product was punctured and released all its contents. No other buckets were damaged and the crew determined it was safe for the driver to continue to his destination. The terminal manager indicated they would offload the freight there and repackage as needed.
column169: NO COMMENTS PROVIDED
